'''Noun'''<br>
'''bovine spongiform encephalopathy'''

== Meaning ==

A fatal, neurodegenerative disease of cattle, which is transmissable to humans through misshaped prion proteins, usually in an epidemic fashion, originated from the [[United Kingdom]]. More commonly known as [[mad cow disease]] or variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease.  Abbreviation: BSE.

